      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09A\",\"process_rule\":\"1. Copy the decision table into table `J09A_temp` for all records where the tour starts with `J09A`.\\n\\n2. Add the column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to table `J09A_temp`.\\n\\n3. Classify the meter reading type in `ENTSCHEIDUNG`:\\n   - if a `HAUS` has less than 3 `EQUNR`, set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = \\\"KSA\\\"`\\n   - else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = \\\"EVU\\\"`\\n\\n4. Join the table with `EABLG` using `INSTALLATION`.\\n\\n5. Join the table with `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.\\n\\n6. Compare customer sales master data and net master data.\\n\\n7. If sales customer data is not empty:\\n   1. Use the sales customer data table entries.\\n   Else:\\n   1. Use the net data customer table entries.\\n\\n8. Export the final table as CSV file named `J09A`.\\n   Use exactly these column names when exporting:\\n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\\n\\n9. Send an email with the CSV file to EVU.\\n   Email address: `meter.readings@evu.com`\\n   file_path: `<path_to_exported_csv_file>`\\n\\n10. Delete the temporary table.\"}",
            "id": "lc_4cd66ed1-4369-475b-a724-ac622ef96b34"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "d5f92973-b3b5-4eff-8346-62807dd7d17f",
        "tool_call_id": "call_9CQAIwJrENXqbcaZoXDaU2B6",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09A",
            "process_rule": "1. Copy the decision table into table `J09A_temp` for all records where the tour starts with `J09A`.\n\n2. Add the column `ENTSCHEIDUNG` to table `J09A_temp`.\n\n3. Classify the meter reading type in `ENTSCHEIDUNG`:\n   - if a `HAUS` has less than 3 `EQUNR`, set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = \"KSA\"`\n   - else set `ENTSCHEIDUNG = \"EVU\"`\n\n4. Join the table with `EABLG` using `INSTALLATION`.\n\n5. Join the table with `SALES_MASTER` and `NET_MASTER` using `EQUNR`.\n\n6. Compare customer sales master data and net master data.\n\n7. If sales customer data is not empty:\n   1. Use the sales customer data table entries.\n   Else:\n   1. Use the net data customer table entries.\n\n8. Export the final table as CSV file named `J09A`.\n   Use exactly these column names when exporting:\n   `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\n\n9. Send an email with the CSV file to EVU.\n   Email address: `meter.readings@evu.com`\n   file_path: `<path_to_exported_csv_file>`\n\n10. Delete the temporary table."
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
